{"parentUuid":"889d59fe-6dbf-4f5d-9c3b-e6084f16621d","isSidechain":true,"userType":"external","cwd":"/home/ryan/formal-conjectures","sessionId":"d1f0a1ae-2e2e-4131-869b-da7f413b2f89","version":"2.1.71","gitBranch":"ai-erdos-7","agentId":"a6e34a10d321d5175","slug":"splendid-questing-bentley","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01YP2y8xNV5qBoQrCS6Lrykv","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/-\n     2→Copyright 2026 The Formal Conjectures Authors.\n     3→\n     4→Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\n     5→you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n     6→You may obtain a copy of the License at\n     7→\n     8→    https://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n     9→\n    10→Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n    11→distributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\n    12→WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n    13→See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n    14→limitations under the License.\n    15→-/\n    16→\n    17→import FormalConjectures.Util.ProblemImports\n    18→\n    19→/-!\n    20→# Erdős Problem 290\n    21→\n    22→*Reference:* [erdosproblems.com/290](https://www.erdosproblems.com/290)\n    23→\n    24→Let $a \\ge 1$. Must there exist some $b > a$ such that\n    25→$$\\sum_{a \\le n \\le b} 1/n = r_1/s_1 \\quad \\text{and} \\quad \\sum_{a \\le n \\le b+1} 1/n = r_2/s_2,$$\n    26→with $(r_i, s_i) = 1$ and $s_2 < s_1$?\n    27→\n    28→For example, $\\sum_{3 \\le n \\le 5} 1/n = 47/60$ and $\\sum_{3 \\le n \\le 6} 1/n = 19/20$,\n    29→and $20 < 60$.\n    30→\n    31→This was resolved in the affirmative by van Doorn [vD24], who proved $b = b(a)$\n    32→always exists and $b(a) \\ll a$. More precisely, $b(a) < 4.374a$ for all $a > 1$,\n    33→and $b(a) > a + 0.54 \\log a$ for all large $a$.\n    34→\n    35→[ErGr80] Erdős, P. and Graham, R., *Old and new problems and results in combinatorial number\n    36→theory*. Monographies de L'Enseignement Mathematique (1980).\n    37→\n    38→[vD24] van Doorn, F., *On the denominators of harmonic numbers* (2024).\n    39→-/\n    40→\n    41→open Finset\n    42→\n    43→namespace Erdos290\n    44→\n    45→/-- The partial harmonic sum $\\sum_{n=a}^{b} 1/n$ as a rational number. -/\n    46→def harmonicPartialSum (a b : ℕ) : ℚ :=\n    47→  (Finset.Icc a b).sum (fun n => (1 : ℚ) / ↑n)\n    48→\n    49→/--\n    50→Erdős Problem 290 (Proved) [ErGr80, p.34]:\n    51→\n    52→For every $a \\ge 1$, there exists $b > a$ such that the denominator of\n    53→$\\sum_{n=a}^{b+1} 1/n$ (in lowest terms) is strictly less than the denominator\n    54→of $\\sum_{n=a}^{b} 1/n$ (in lowest terms).\n    55→-/\n    56→@[category research solved, AMS 11]\n    57→theorem erdos_290 : answer(True) ↔\n    58→    ∀ a : ℕ, 1 ≤ a →\n    59→    ∃ b : ℕ, a < b ∧\n    60→      (harmonicPartialSum a (b + 1)).den < (harmonicPartialSum a b).den := by\n    61→  sorry\n    62→\n    63→end Erdos290\n    64→"}]},"uuid":"4ac86e7a-f307-4599-a702-30ce40c377e3","timestamp":"2026-03-10T05:29:07.824Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"889d59fe-6dbf-4f5d-9c3b-e6084f16621d"}
